The paper deals with the problem of storage allocation and reallocation in databases, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents algorithms for minimizing the storage footprint and reallocation costs, which are relevant to several subfields of computer science. Specifically, the paper deals with data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), algorithms (cs.AL), distributed computing (cs.DC), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
